This paper deals with maintaining high resource availability in a networked multi-robot system, which is a core problem in the field of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also proposes a method that uses integer semi-definite programming to achieve the goal of reconfiguring the network after a resource failure, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY). The paper also mentions the use of simulated annealing, which is a common optimization technique used in machine learning (cs.MA) and the paper deals with communication topology, which is a topic in networked systems (cs.NI). Finally, the paper proposes a method for joint task planning, which is a common problem in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
